cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the task of multi-class segmentation of anatomical structures in chest radiographs using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of different loss functions and pre-trained encoder weights, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The application of the proposed method is in the medical field, which suggests the possibility of cs.MED (Medical Imaging) as a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a benchmark dataset and evaluates the performance of the proposed method, which is a common practice in the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
